<item>
            <title>[LU-13396] lustre 2.12.4 client rpmbuild error</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13396</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;i rebuild 2.12.4 clients in centos 7.6 use command line :&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
rpmbuild --rebuild --without servers lustre-2.12.4-1.src.rpm
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;no error found while configure, but when compiling , i see error&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
Processing files: lustre-client-tests-2.12.4-1.el7.x86_64
error: File not found by glob: /root/rpmbuild/BUILDROOT/lustre-2.12.4-1.x86_64/usr/lib64/openmpi/bin/*

&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So why openmpi needed but can not found ? how can I walkarround this ?&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;PS: i rebuild 2.12.2 client in the same sever , everything goes fine.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>centos 7.6&lt;br/&gt;
mofed 4.6</environment>
